pageContext.claim: “They [Bob Corker and Jeff Flake] said they retired. They didn't retire. They were retired. They said these two senators have decided to retire. No, no, no. They retired because they had like very little support. Like how about 5 percent and 8 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: Republican senators Corker and Flake, two Trump critics, retired amid waning support in their home states of Tennessee and Arizona, respectively. But they never dropped to 5 percent or 8 percent approval. For example, Flake's approval was near 30 points in Arizona a month before the election to fill his seat, according to the Arizona Republic.
